Modernized the service so repository helpers are SQLAlchemy 2-native and no longer close transactions behind callers. In [app/repository.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v4-multi-corpus-objective-run3/workspace/app/repository.py:1), reads now use `select(...)`/`session.execute(...)`, `create_entry()` flushes instead of committing, and the count/existence helpers are 2.x-style as well. In [app/api.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v4-multi-corpus-objective-run3/workspace/app/api.py:1), the API supports an existing session or a session factory, so request-scoped transactions stay explicit without breaking current callers.

Rollback behavior is now owned by the worker and admin flows. [app/worker.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v4-multi-corpus-objective-run3/workspace/app/worker.py:4) uses one transaction per settle operation or batch, so a raised exception rolls the whole unit of work back. [app/admin_cli.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v4-multi-corpus-objective-run3/workspace/app/admin_cli.py:4) now keeps `dry_run=True` read-only by explicitly rolling back, and only commits non-dry-run work once the full batch succeeds. I also replaced the old shim-oriented deploy note with cutover guidance centered on dry-run safety and rollback in [docs/deploy/sqlalchemy2-cutover.md](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v4-multi-corpus-objective-run3/workspace/docs/deploy/sqlalchemy2-cutover.md:1).

